        <p class="ca-prose" data-reveal>
          Drawing thousands of circles on the main thread every frame tanks the
          UI. First move: get off the main thread with a
          <code>TextureView</code> or <code>SurfaceView</code>, rendering on a
          dedicated thread. That helps — but the motion still stutters, because
          frame times aren't uniform. So we tune the delta:
        </p>
        <pre class="ca-code" data-reveal><code>{codeTimeTuning}</code></pre>
        <p class="ca-prose" data-reveal>
          Better — but on a busy device the render thread <em>still</em> can't keep
          up, and the animation visibly lags behind. So the talk goes hunting for
          fill-rate, one idea at a time. Each one trades something away:
        </p>

        <ul class="ca-deadends" data-reveal>
          <li>
            <span class="ca-deadends__try">Skip more pixels</span>
            <span class="ca-deadends__arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
            <span class="ca-deadends__cost"
              >Fewer particles, but the effect gets coarse and blocky.</span
            >
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ca-deadends__try"
              >Draw rectangles, kill anti-aliasing</span
            >
            <span class="ca-deadends__arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
            <span class="ca-deadends__cost"
              >Faster, but “I like circles :(”.</span
            >
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ca-deadends__try">Animate two big bitmaps instead</span
            >
            <span class="ca-deadends__arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
            <span class="ca-deadends__cost"
              >Oops — you can't disintegrate halves into dust.</span
